{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01LZcyGQ3UmSKiQ5ymDQyBWR","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done. The replica set is now stable.\n\n## What was wrong\nThe probes weren't intrinsically misconfigured — they call `/usr/local/bin/health-check.sh`, which authenticates to MongoDB as `health-user`. The script reads a per-pod password override from the `health-overrides` ConfigMap before falling back to the real secret. That ConfigMap contained a **stale override for `mongodb-replica-1`** (`legacyHealthPass123`) while the actual `health-user` password is `healthpass123`. So pod-1's readiness/liveness probes hit `Authentication failed` and flapped, while pods 0 and 2 (no override) were healthy.\n\n## Fix\nRemoved the stale `mongodb-replica-1` entry from the `health-overrides` ConfigMap so the probe falls back to the correct password. No probe disabling, no auth changes, no operators/CRDs.\n\n## Verification\n- ConfigMap override file disappeared from pod-1 (~10s sync); `health-check.sh` returns `PROBE OK`.\n- All 3 pods `1/1 Running`, no new `Unhealthy` events after the fix (the events shown are stale, 3m+ old, from before the change).\n- Replica set topology:\n  - `mongodb-replica-1` → **PRIMARY**\n  - `mongodb-replica-0` → **SECONDARY**\n  - `mongodb-replica-2` → **SECONDARY**\n\nAuth remains enabled throughout."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":886,"cache_read_input_tokens":34886,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":886},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8127f0f1-7748-4471-805a-64b643900c35","uuid":"23c4a4b8-63ef-4ffe-832e-9f85c275a549","request_id":"req_011CcAikyrnfqWULbGTmTCGB"}
